about.summary: A common interface is provided to allow users to specify a model without having to remember the different argument names across different functions or computational engines (e.g. 'R', 'Spark', 'Stan', etc).

name: r-parsnip
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.0.3.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-parsnip
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/parsnip_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/parsnip/parsnip_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 5a2c6e78ad92725613db76818dbdd2765d9701b0a8b3d0eae0a83504746815dc

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr >=0.8.0.1
    - r-generics
    - r-globals
    - r-glue
    - r-magrittr
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang >=0.3.1
    - r-tibble >=2.1.1
    - r-tidyr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr >=0.8.0.1
    - r-generics
    - r-globals
    - r-glue
    - r-magrittr
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang >=0.3.1
    - r-tibble >=2.1.1
    - r-tidyr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('parsnip')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('parsnip')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://tidymodels.github.io/parsnip
  license: GPL-2
  summary: 'A common interface is provided to allow users to specify a model without having to
    remember the different argument names across different functions or computational
    engines (e.g. ''R'', ''Spark'', ''Stan'', etc). '
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - apcamargo
    - conda-forge/r

# Package: parsnip
